Package music

Class Document

java.lang.Object
music.Document
public class Document extends Object
This class represents a whole mei piece of music. It has a list of Measures objects, and can output the interval of the notes in the document. Also contains metadata

    • outputInterval

      public void outputInterval(File outfile) throws IOException
      Outputs the respective interval for this 'document', or piece of music.
      Parameters:
      outfile - the file we are outputting the interval to
      Throws:
      IOException - when there is an issue with the files

    • getIntervalsFromMeasures

      public void getIntervalsFromMeasures()
      Computes and populates the intervalRep array with interval values derived from adjacent pairs of Measure objects in the measures list. Each measure computes its interval relative to the next one in sequence, or null if it is the last measure.
      See Also:
      • Measure.getMeasureInterval(Measure)

    • getMeasureMap

      public int[] getMeasureMap()
      Generates a mapping from each musical note or chord to the index of its containing measure. Only objects of type Note or Chord are considered.
      Returns:
      an array of measure indices corresponding to the order of Note and Chord instances in measures
      See Also:
      • Note
      • Chord
